<h4>Building It</h4>

The biggest problem i had was the freaking small case and don't get me wrong, the case is very slick and i love
the small footprint/feature ratio, but it is very difficult to work with. To install everything in this case you
absolutely need to take everything apart first. For example, In order to change just the optical drive, you will
need to remove all components of the case including the motherboard. For that reason, I used&nbsp;<span
        style="background-color: white;">a completely modular power supply, even the big ATX connector, so that&nbsp;</span>I
can easily remove the unit without having to disconnect any cable on the board. It's quite a tight fit so you
don't want to have to open it often.<br/>
